   "source": [
    "# 02 - LangChain Tools\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the custom LangChain tools created for Polymarket analysis and trading."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "from polymarket_agents.tools.market_tools import fetch_active_markets, get_market_details\n",
    "from polymarket_agents.tools.research_tools import web_search, market_news_search, comprehensive_research\n",
    "from polymarket_agents.tools.trade_tools import execute_market_order, execute_limit_order\n",
    "from pprint import pprint\n",
    "\n",
    "load_dotenv(override=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Market Tools\n",
    "\n",
    "These tools allow the LLM to discover and inspect markets."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fetch active markets\n",
    "active_markets = fetch_active_markets.run(tool_input={"limit": 3})\n",
    "pprint(active_markets)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Research Tools\n",
    "\n",
    "Research tools integrate with external APIs like Tavily to gather news and context."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Perform a web search\n",
    "search_results = web_search.run(tool_input={"query": "Polymarket trading volume 2025"})\n",
    "pprint(search_results)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Market specific news search\n",
    "if active_markets and 'error' not in active_markets[0]:\n",
    "    market_q = active_markets[0]['question']\n",
    "    news = market_news_search.run(tool_input={"market_question": market_q})\n",
    "    print(f\"News for: {market_q}\")\n",
    "    pprint(news)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Trade Tools\n",
    "\n",
    "These tools allow the agent to execute trades (use with caution!)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
